cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence-to-sequence generation and language translation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a technique for improving model performance. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with natural language processing and generation. The paper also proposes structural changes to the Transformer architecture, which could make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's experiments involve language translation, which could make it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well.
